<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>why PvP is doomed...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?dylan waite">dylan waite</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:11 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> why PvP is doomed...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>when Verant sat down and made this game in the first place, they wanted to make a very ROLEPLAYING oriented game.......i'm not saying this is good or bad, it's just the way it is....they set out to build a online COMMUNITY....these are guys who seem to have played endless MUD's and have made EQ very much like the MUD's they have played......MUD's are also about community......

<P>now the problem with this in regardes to PvP is that PvP is not a community (at least not as defined by the sensiblities of the rest of the world)......to "normal" players, you guys appear to be people who want to destroy any sense of community they may exist and the sad truth is, the guys who made the game are the "normal" players.......
<P>to "normal" players, UO was a game that was overrun by k3wLd00d l33t Hax0R69 types and sucked miserably....i understand that you guys enjoyed it, fair enough.......now, not to be speaking on behalf of the dev team, but it sure as shit seems to me that most of the rules set forth in EQ thus far have been solely to control the k3wLd00d l33t Hax0R69's out there and not allow them to ruin anyone else's game, which is what you did in UO.....u took UO and made it fun for yourselves at the expense of everyone who wasn't one of you...OSI tried to stop you for some time, but since you were so l33t (hahaha) you found ways to exploit the system, you found work-arounds to any anti-PK mechanism that was implemented and continued to ruin the game for the "normal" player....you basically took what was supposed to be a roleplaying game and turned it into a stupid frag-fest action game.....OSI was too dumb to stop you and was eventually forced to play ball your way (because you were the only paying customers left after having driven away all the "normal" players)....
<P>to you guys UO was about how BAD you could be....it was a huge pissing contest to see who could slaughter the most newbies, and who could behave in the most antisocial way possible...this is what you liked about the game...the way to "win" in UO seems to have been to be more famous for being a prick than the next guy (that's all i've heard anyone say on this board for the last couple of days)....i don't pretend to understand it, but i guess i have to respect it.........my problem with what you did to UO was when people called you out for being snot-nosed, jr high kids and you chose (for the most part) to defend your style of gameplay by asserting how "in-character" and "roleplaying" slaughtering hoardes of innocents was because you were "roleplaying" an evil character.......sigh.......you all know as well as i do that the notion of a world populated entirely by serial killers is the most unrealistic thing there is.....again, OSI's fault for not making their world real enough....you see, kiddies, in the real world when bad people do bad things, they are PUNISHED...and, typically, the punishment reflects the seriousness of the crime....murder being one of the more serious offences, any logically thinking human being would conclude that the punishment for murder would be pretty damn stiff...it wasn't...in fact, it wasn't punished to any legitimate degree at all and in the popular culture on UO servers, it was encouraged and admired....EQ knows better
<P>EQ has not made the same errors in game design that made your vision of "serial killer land" possible....you will have to live with this...waht made UO fun for you was , in fact, just a clinic in poor design.....Verant has taken the time to make, IMHO, a pretty damned realistic world in which your actions , both dastardly and saintly, seem to have some very real affect on your ability to play the game....this is GOOD...good in the sense that peopel in Norrath will be forced to behave within certain guidelines just like people in teh real world are forced to behave within certain guidelines.......now you'll all say "...but i don't want no r00ls, that shIt is for FaGs....i WaNnA d0 wHAt i WanT....If I WanT to r0l3Play a eViLL(tm) cHar, Th3N i ShouLd b3 abL3 to".....the truth is, you want to play quake, and you want to force everyone to play quake with you.......killing anyone who happens to walk by is NOT roleplaying....roleplaying is behaving the way you believe your character would behave in some fantasy setting......in any reasonable society people are punished for killing innocents....you char would know this before he started killin innocents and wouldn't do it...if he did, he would be punished severly (prolly killed, which would make your in-game experince a little different, eh?)....
<P>so NOW, you jokers are placed into a situation where you will be forced to roleplay, where the world will fight back(just like the real world) against it's criminal element and you're all crying the blues about it....well cry me a river, monkey boy, cause that's the way it is.....maybe this PvP server is a good idea after all, it's actually a brilliant move on Verant's part...they can quarantine al you assholes and isolate you from people who want to actually play Everquest as opposed to EverQuake......for the cost of another server and whatever they're paying geiger, they can maintain their initial game-design vision without the likes of you ruining it for everyone else nd turn it into something it's not supposed to be.....
<P>so, in a sense, you win.....you get your "serial killer world"....have at it, jerk off.....but for god's sake if i see one more post on this board demanding that Verant re-write all their code to amke the game more fun for you guys, i'll go mad.........in this case, my friends, you guys are the minority...the game wasn't designed with you in mind and won't be re-written to accomodate you...you're lucky enough that you have your own server
<P>in the end, i believe PvP is doomed........Verant will NOT re-write huge chunks of code (basically, what you seem to be asking is for them to throw their whole level/skills out the window and re-do it just for you) to accomodate you (whom "normal" players consider to be a very annoying degnerate case)......you d00ds are typical regarded as a probelm that a game must be designed around....the bottom line is that Verant, in all likeliehood, will honor NONE of your requsts and you'll be playing the game, in respect to PvP, just as it is now for a good long time .......there just simply isn't enough time to develop two games concurrently and you'll be the ones that are sacrificed for the good of the other........once the light of day fianlly filters thru your thick skulls and you REALIZE that PvP was put into ths game as an afterthought and this REALLY isn't meant to be a PvP game, you'll get bored (hopefully) and go back to UO or wherever it is you came from and probably talk shit about what a horrible game this was for years to come (..much like the way us "normal" players still talk shit abou how bad UO sucked to this day).........maybe i'm wrong, maybe Verant will spawn a daughter company (VerantPvP inc) to re-write the entire game so that the degenarate case 10% of the market will also buy it along with the "normal" players........but i wouldn't hold my breath ;)
<P>ps ...the sad truth is that i initially cam onto this board as an advocate of PvP....i didn't believe that the k3wL d00d HaXoR69's really were so prevalent in the PvP "community".......i was really hoping i'd find some mature, intelligent people who could understand the diffence between in-character PvP and EverQuake.......i have obviously been shown the error of my ways and now humbly go back to join the "normal" players.......as much as i liked the idea of more developed PvP, i find that i must sacrifice that to keep all the k3wL d00d HaXoR69's away from me so i can just play the damn game MY way and not be forced to adapt my style to your style (...and in so doing, givivng up many of the things i find fun about the game just to survive).....enjoy your server and have a nice day ;)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
